article.description: Elijah Wilson had 25 points and seven rebounds, Ron Trapps made five 3-pointers and finished with 17 points, and Coastal Carolina beat Piedmont International 116-35 on Saturday.
article.headline: Wilson, Coastal Carolina beat Piedmont International 116-35
article.linkText: Wilson, Coastal Carolina beat Piedmont International 116-35
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- Elijah Wilson had 25 points and seven rebounds, Ron Trapps made five 3-pointers and finished with 17 points, and Coastal Carolina beat Piedmont International 116-35 on Saturday. It was the second straight 100-plus scoring game for Coastal Carolina after a 104-67 win over Grace Bible on Wednesday. Michel Enanga had 16 points and eight rebounds for Coastal Carolina (2-2). The Chanticleers made 61 percent of their field goals, including 13 of 31 3-pointers and won the rebounding battle 59-22. Coastal Carolina opened the game with a 9-0 run and had a 16-0 run later in the first half. The Chanticleers led 60-11 at halftime and opened the second half by outscoring Piedmont 32-12. Timothy Worles hit four 3-pointers and scored 18 points for Piedmont International. The Bruins were held to 12-of-61 shooting (20 percent).
